\f0\fs21\fsmilli10667 Summing up the results of our empirical investigation, it can be stated that Zipf\'92s law is rejected for poland in every case, unless a special threshold is used. thus, it is necessary to reject the hypothesis that Zipf\'92s law is a good description of the population distribution of polish cities. the estimated exponent is above unity, which means that the distribution of polish city sizes is more uneven than Zipf\'92s law predicts, while the estimated constant differs significantly from the log of the largest city in every case. 
